        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 7:56PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 756 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Owego, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Campville, Apalachin, Chenango Valley State Park, Conklin, Tioga
Terrace, Endicott, Maine, Chenango Forks, Newark Valley, and Port
Dickinson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
